But explain to me exactly why that breaks a system.

27:44.120 --> 27:48.060
It creates an over-determined, non-invertible representation.

27:49.720 --> 27:52.080
Let's trace the logic of their own claims.

27:52.320 --> 27:59.400
Let's say emotion shifts the phase of the wave, meaning it pushes the wave slightly left or right on a graph.

27:59.400 --> 28:13.700
If that's true, then two identical memories, say eating a hamburger that just happened to have different emotional contexts, like eating it joyfully versus eating it sadly, will be out of phase.

28:13.800 --> 28:15.660
Right, because the emotion pushed them.

28:15.800 --> 28:19.200
Because they are out of phase, they will destructively interfere.

28:19.600 --> 28:20.960
Maybe that's what MAM-8 wanted.

28:20.960 --> 28:34.320
But if emotion also shifts the amplitude, the physical height of the wave, then the resulting interference pattern becomes a tangled, chaotic mess of both phase and magnitude dependencies.

28:34.640 --> 28:35.640
It just becomes noise.

28:35.920 --> 28:36.360
Exactly.

28:36.360 --> 28:46.580
If an AI tries to read that superposed, jumbled signal later to retrieve the memory, it is mathematically impossible to reconstruct the original inputs.

28:47.060 --> 28:48.820
You cannot untangle the knot.

28:49.180 --> 28:51.000
Information is permanently lost.

28:51.160 --> 28:53.120
So how does RSVP solve this?

28:53.820 --> 28:59.400
How do we encode sadness into a math field without breaking the ability to retrieve the memory?

28:59.840 --> 29:04.940
Through an advanced geometric concept called foliation of the plenum state space.

29:04.940 --> 29:07.860
Foliation sounds botanical.

29:08.280 --> 29:12.140
It does, but in geometry, it's about dividing a space into layers.

29:12.980 --> 29:22.940
Instead of treating emotion as a random variable that tweaks the height or speed of a single wave, the RSVP framework treats emotional context as a submanifold.

29:23.720 --> 29:23.940
A submanifold.

29:24.620 --> 29:31.140
A distinct separate geometric layer within the total massive space of all possible field configurations.

29:31.140 --> 29:35.900
Let's call a specific emotional context, like sadness, E.

29:36.800 --> 29:40.920
This context defines a specific submanifold, M subscript E.

29:41.060 --> 29:41.260
Okay.

29:41.380 --> 29:48.900
When you encode a memory while experiencing that emotion, you're mathematically projecting the memory strictly onto that specific submanifold.

29:49.240 --> 29:49.480
Okay.

29:49.560 --> 29:51.140
If you're listening, let's visualize this.

29:51.760 --> 29:55.600
It's like a massive multi-story parking garage.

29:55.900 --> 29:58.820
The entire garage represents the mind.

29:59.040 --> 29:59.780
I like this.

29:59.780 --> 30:09.840
In MemMate's flawed system, Joy was a bumper sticker you slapped on a car, and maybe it also controlled how fast the car was driving.

30:10.020 --> 30:10.720
It was chaotic.

30:11.320 --> 30:16.180
But in RSVP, Joy is the entire third floor of the garage.

30:16.340 --> 30:16.640
Yes.

30:16.640 --> 30:20.500
You park the memory securely on the floor that matches the emotion.

30:20.860 --> 30:29.080
When it's time to retrieve a happy memory, you don't have to wander through the entire garage scanning every single car for a Joy bumper sticker.

30:29.280 --> 30:33.340
You just take the elevator straight to the third floor and look at the cars parked there.

30:33.600 --> 30:34.120
Exactly.

30:34.420 --> 30:36.260
The emotion is the space.

30:36.260 --> 30:44.300
And if we connect this to the bigger picture, this links perfectly back to the rat brain anesthesia study we spent so much time on earlier.

30:44.420 --> 30:45.220
Oh, wait, how?

30:45.380 --> 30:52.900
Remember how the changing biophysical state of the anesthetized brain changed which wave modes were physically accessible?

30:52.900 --> 30:53.500
Yes.

30:53.720 --> 30:58.160
The waves literally collapsed as the deep anesthesia flooded the tissue.

30:58.820 --> 31:03.820
That is the biological correlate of this emotional submanifold concept.

31:04.800 --> 31:09.880
Emotion in a biological brain isn't a post-it note attached to a memory wave.

31:10.300 --> 31:14.820
It is a profound change in the biophysical state of the chemical medium itself.

31:15.140 --> 31:15.940
Oh, wow.

31:15.940 --> 31:20.920
The emotion determines which dynamic spaces are physically accessible to the neurons.

31:21.940 --> 31:26.780
Deep anesthesia is a literal change in the geometry of the accessible space.

31:27.640 --> 31:39.420
By treating emotion as a foliation, a distinct geometric layer, RSVP is perfectly mirroring the actual physical constraints of a biological nervous system.

31:39.420 --> 31:41.580
That is a staggering realization.

31:41.980 --> 31:49.300
And it leads perfectly into how we bridge these emotional wave-like sub-symbolic states back to traditional computing.

31:49.480 --> 31:55.600
Because the paper spends time discussing the interface between symbolic and sub-symbolic computation.

31:56.120 --> 31:59.640
It calls this the CyForge versus I-verse stack.

31:59.760 --> 31:59.900
Right.

32:00.040 --> 32:01.680
We have two very different worlds here.

32:01.820 --> 32:01.920
Oh.

32:02.100 --> 32:06.000
Traditional AI like ChatGPT or any LLM is purely symbolic.

32:06.200 --> 32:07.880
It's state compute output.

32:07.880 --> 32:10.980
It deals in rigid words, logic, and discrete tokens.

32:11.120 --> 32:11.780
Like a calculator.

32:12.240 --> 32:12.660
Exactly.

32:13.620 --> 32:16.280
But the RSVP plenum is sub-symbolic.

32:16.820 --> 32:20.960
It deals in continuous fields, interactions, and reconstructions.

32:21.260 --> 32:22.780
You cannot just mask them together.

32:23.320 --> 32:27.460
The paper rigorously defines two projection operators to act as translators.

32:28.200 --> 32:35.540
Phi, which maps symbolic text into the wave plenum, and Psi, which maps the wave back out into symbolic text.

32:35.540 --> 32:38.680
And the paper points out something crucial about these translators.

32:39.040 --> 32:50.980
If you take a sharp symbolic thought, map it down into the emotional wave plenum, and then map it back out to a symbolic thought, you do not always get the exact same sentence back.

32:51.100 --> 32:51.900
No, you don't.

32:51.900 --> 32:57.720
The mathematical equation is Psi of Phi of Y is approximately Y. It's an approximation.

32:58.260 --> 33:04.760
And we must stress, this isn't a bug. It is a feature. It is a mechanism called semantic grounding.

33:04.760 --> 33:17.460
If the rigid symbolic LLM system generates concepts that the physical continuous wave dynamics cannot actually sustain or differentiate, those fragile concepts will be naturally lost in round trip.

33:17.680 --> 33:18.640
They get filtered out.

33:18.960 --> 33:19.220
Yes.

33:19.560 --> 33:30.100
The loss actually reveals to the AI which parts of its symbolic logic are grounded in physical dynamical reality, and which are just arbitrary linguistic conventions.

33:30.100 --> 33:43.780
It's like taking a very dry technical English legal document, translating it into a highly poetic, context-heavy language like ancient Sanskrit, and then translating it back to English.

33:43.980 --> 33:45.440
That's a great way to think about it.

33:45.640 --> 33:57.680
You might lose some of the dry technical precision, but you find out very quickly which core fundamental human meanings survive the cultural and linguistic shift.

33:57.680 --> 34:06.000
Exactly. And the projection operators must respect that entropy closure we talked about with your dinner party analogy.

34:06.140 --> 34:06.380
Right.

34:06.700 --> 34:21.180
If two-wave memories are fundamentally incompatible in the plenum, like if the vegans and the metalheads can't share the room, their symbolic translations must also be logically inconsistent in the symbolic LLM layer.

34:21.180 --> 34:27.540
The two domains, the waves and the words, have to respect each other's underlying rules.

34:28.000 --> 34:33.840
Okay, so this RSVP system is incredibly rigorous, it's biologically inspired, and it's mathematically sound.

34:34.340 --> 34:43.440
But when the creators of MEM8 were challenged by the wider community on the vagueness of their math, they didn't pivot to something rigorous like RSVP.

34:43.480 --> 34:44.180
No, they didn't.

