But look at your orientation. Because you walked on a curved surface, when you arrived back at the north pole, you were facing a completely different direction than when you started.

39:52.120 --> 39:53.880
Your orientation has twisted.

39:54.100 --> 39:59.700
Oh, because the surface itself forced me to turn differently relative to space.

39:59.820 --> 40:08.700
Exactly. That twist, that geometric failure to return to your original state after traveling a closed loop, that is holonomy failure.

40:08.700 --> 40:11.260
Oh, that is brilliant.

40:12.040 --> 40:29.800
Okay, so applying this to memory, if the mathematical space of the memory system is curved or warped by, say, intense emotion, a sequence of logical thoughts, the path you walk, might seem totally correct locally at every single step.

40:29.880 --> 40:31.720
Yes. Step by step, it feels right.

