But when you complete the thought and try to connect it back to your core beliefs, you end up with a twisted, completely incompatible conclusion.

40:40.840 --> 40:44.300
Memmates' memories are twisting when they try to connect across boundaries.

40:44.520 --> 40:46.200
Exactly. You've nailed it.

40:46.620 --> 40:50.640
And to measure this, the Flyxion paper introduces the Amplet-WIS framework.

40:51.220 --> 40:54.880
It calculates something called the vorticity of the phase-weighted field.

40:55.340 --> 40:56.920
Vorticity. Like a vortex.

40:56.920 --> 41:05.340
Right. If you measure high vorticity at a layer boundary, it means there is high curvature, which guarantees a holonomy failure.

41:05.800 --> 41:12.640
It means the cascade of memories cannot smoothly compose without a jarring phase discontinuity.

41:13.040 --> 41:20.460
And here is the crucial difference between MEM8's fake math salad and the Amplet-WIS framework.

41:20.860 --> 41:23.720
Your catchphrase applies here perfectly.

